      {"question_id":"dl_beg_002","type":"true_false","question":"Batch normalisation helps speed up training by normalising layer inputs, reducing internal covariate shift.","correct_answer":True,"explanation":"BatchNorm normalises each mini-batch's activations to zero mean and unit variance, stabilising training. This allows higher learning rates and reduces sensitivity to weight initialisation, speeding up convergence significantly.","difficulty_score":3,"time_seconds":30,"tags":["batch_normalisation","training","convergence"],"prerequisites":["dl_beg_001"],"common_mistakes":["Thinking BatchNorm only regularises, not speeds up training"],"learning_resources":["https://arxiv.org/abs/1502.03167"],"real_world_context":"BatchNorm is used in ResNets, BERT, and essentially all production deep learning models."},
